{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"51a263e4-4be8-4cad-b028-b29823ca32aa","content":"No existing files found, so I'll provide the solution directly.\n\n## Compiled Bindings in .NET MAUI\n\nThe key change is adding `x:DataType` to your XAML, which tells the compiler the type of `BindingContext` so bindings are validated **at build time** instead of resolved at runtime via reflection.\n\n### SettingsPage.xaml — before → after\n\nAdd these two things:\n\n1. **An `xmlns` for your ViewModel namespace**\n2. **`x:DataType=\"viewmodels:SettingsViewModel\"` on the root element**\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:viewmodels=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"viewmodels:SettingsViewModel\"\n             Title=\"Settings\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Label Text=\"Theme\" />\n        <Entry Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <Label Text=\"Enable Notifications\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n\n        <Label Text=\"Font Size\" />\n        <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"48\" Increment=\"1\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='Current size: {0}'}\" />\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThat's it — every `{Binding …}` under that `x:DataType` scope is now **compiled**.\n\n### How binding errors are caught at build time\n\nWith `x:DataType` set, the XAML compiler will emit **build errors** (not warnings) if you:\n\n- Reference a property that doesn't exist (e.g., `{Binding Thme}` — typo)\n- Bind to a property with an incompatible type\n\nYou'll see errors like:\n\n```\nXC0045: Binding: Property \"Thme\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\".\n```\n\n### Opting out for a specific binding\n\nIf you need a runtime-resolved binding somewhere (e.g., a `TemplateBinding` or dynamic context), locally disable compiled bindings:\n\n```xml\n<Label Text=\"{Binding SomeDynamicProp}\" x:DataType=\"{x:Null}\" />\n```\n\n### Summary\n\n| Step | What to do |\n|---|---|\n| **1** | Add `xmlns` alias for the ViewModel namespace |\n| **2** | Add `x:DataType=\"viewmodels:SettingsViewModel\"` to `<ContentPage>` |\n| **3** | Build — any misspelled or wrong-type bindings become **compile errors** |\n| **4** | Use `x:DataType=\"{x:Null}\"` to opt out where needed |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3a5fdfce-b737-4d90-b562-dc4b17d9c7dd","outputTokens":719,"requestId":"F3C7:20AC41:1EA63FD:226E8EC:69E81959"},"id":"54bf4658-e619-4004-a5e5-66eec8d89a82","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:42:16.873Z","parentId":"738f342f-c427-4639-8471-5985495c2ebc"}
